# Cursor Settings Rules

## Manual approach (current default)

The gateway does **not** automatically modify Cursor's `state.vscdb`. You set
three things manually in Cursor Settings → Models:

| Setting                       | Value                                                                          |
| ----------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| OpenAI API Key                | Gateway key from `start` JSON (`gateway_key`) or `status` JSON (`gateway_key_masked` to verify) |
| Override OpenAI Base URL      | `https://<your-tunnel-host>/v1` (or your BYO HTTPS URL)                       |
| Model                         | An alias from the model table below (e.g. `gpt-5-high`, `gpt-4o-mini`)    |

**Provider choice is the alias** (Kimi vs DeepSeek) — Cursor still talks only to
the gateway; never to Moonshot/DeepSeek directly.

## Model alias table

Primary Agent-safe aliases (see `gateway.mdc` for full map):

| Alias            | →                                              |
| ---------------- | ---------------------------------------------- |
| `gpt-5-high` | Moonshot `kimi-k3` (planning)                  |
| `gpt-5-codex`    | Moonshot `kimi-k2.6` (image-capable)         |
| `gpt-4o`         | DeepSeek `deepseek-v4-pro` (execution)         |
| `gpt-4o-mini`    | DeepSeek `deepseek-v4-flash` (cheap execution) |

Do not use `claude-*` / `gemini-*` names on the OpenAI override path.

## Why manual?

- Cursor's `secret://cursorAuth/openAIKey` storage differs between versions
- Troubleshooting is easier when you can toggle the override in the UI
- You can switch between Cursor's own models and the gateway quickly

## `Cursor private network forbidden`

| Symptom                                    | Cause                                 | Fix                                                                           |
| ------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Base URL to localhost fails / SSRF blocked | Cursor cloud cannot reach private IPs | Use public HTTPS tunnel or BYO URL (`tunnel.mdc`); never "fix" with 127.0.0.1 |

